    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP" source="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Φιλόξενε</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/>χρηστὲ χαῖρε
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after Orsi 1912, 1915 and inventory</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>Orsi 1912: ΧΡΗΤ (sic); corrected in inventory and 1915</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Farewell, worthy Philoxenos!</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text was inadvertently published twice by Orsi in the NSA; the sigma is inserted subsequently in the transcription in the inventory, and clearly was omitted in the first transcription and the initial publication. The stone has not yet been located in the museum.</p>
            </div>
